{"questionId":"25760791","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The admissions team at a new university are trying to predict the number of student&nbsp;applications they will receive each year.</p>\n<p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> be the number of years that the university has been open. The admissions team collect the following data for the first two years.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/0d0fd473258347545caf6a7a1bfc24be107809cc.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>It is assumed that the number of students that apply to the university each year will follow a&nbsp;geometric sequence, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the common ratio of the sequence.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>03</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<br><strong>Note:</strong> Follow through from part (a).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25760791","referenceCode":"21N.2.SL.TZ0.2b.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the common ratio of the sequence.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.2—Arithmetic sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.3—Geometric sequences and series","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Approximating and estimating"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}